@section Remote Controls

Bino supports remote controls via @url{http://www.lirc.org/,LIRC}.

Use the client name @samp{bino} in your LIRC configuration. The default LIRC
configuration file usually is @code{~/.lircrc}. You can use the
@samp{--lirc-config} option to use one or more custom LIRC configuration files
instead.

The available commands are the same commands that are available for scripting.
@xref{Script Commands}.

Example LIRC configuration file excerpt:
@example
begin
  remote = ...
  button = ...
  prog   = bino
  config = adjust-brightness +0.05
end
@end example


@node Scripting
@chapter Scripting

Bino can read commands from one or multiple script files. Use the @samp{--read-commands}
option to specify script files.

Available script commands are listed below. @xref{Script Commands}.

A script file can be a standard text file, but it can also be a named pipe,
which allows other programs or scripts to submit commands to Bino as they see
fit.

@example
$ mkfifo ~/bino-command-fifo
$ bino --read-commands ~/bino-command-fifo &

$ echo 'set-contrast 0.1' > ~/bino-command-fifo
$ ...
@end example

Using the @samp{netcat} utility, this also works over the network.

@example
$ mkfifo ~/bino-command-fifo
$ bino --read-commands ~/bino-command-fifo &

$ nc -l 1234 > ~/bino-command-fifo &
$ telnet localhost 1234
set-contrast 0.1
...
@end example

Here is a simple example script file:
@example
# Play all videos in fullscreen mode.
toggle-fullscreen
# Open the first video.
open /path/to/video.webm
# Start playing.
play
# Wait until the video finishes before continuing this script.
wait stop
# Open a second video. This one has a space in its file name.
open /path/to/video%20file.webm
# Start playing.
play
# Immediately increase brightness.
adjust-brightness +0.1
# Immediately seek to 60 seconds within the video.
seek 60.0
# Let the video play for 30.0 seconds before continuing with this script.
wait 30.0
# Open a third video. This one has left and right view in separate files.
open /path/to/left.webm /path/to/right.webm
# Start playing.
play
@end example

This script is executed with the following command. The @samp{--no-gui} option
is not necessary, but prevents the GUI to remember the changed brightness
setting in future sessions.
@example
$ bino --read-commands /path/to/script.txt --no-gui
@end example

@section Script Commands
@anchor{Script Commands}

One script line defines exactly one script command.  Empty lines or lines
starting with the @samp{#} character are comment lines and define the
@samp{noop} command, which has no effect.

@table @samp
@item noop
This command has no effect.
@item quit
Quit the application.
@item wait @var{stop}|@var{seconds}
Wait until the currently playing video stops, or wait for the given number of seconds,
before processing more commands from this file, script, or FIFO.@*
(This command is not available for LIRC remote controls.)
@item open [@var{option}@dots{}] @var{file}@dots{}
Open the given files.@*
You can use percent-encoding to encode special characters.
See @url{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Percent_encoding}.
Use this if the file names contain whitespace.@*
To open devices, the following options are available, analogous to the command
line options with the same name:
	@table @samp
	@item --device-type=@var{none}|@var{default}|@var{firewire}|@var{x11}
	@item --device-frame-size=@var{W}x@var{H}
	@item --device-frame-rate=@var{N}/@var{D}
	@item --device-format=@var{default}|@var{mjpeg}
	@end table
@item close
Close the currently opened input.
@item toggle-play
Toggle playback.
@item play
Start playback, or exit pause mode.
@item stop
Stop playback.
@item toggle-pause
Toggle pause mode.
@item pause
When playing, go into pause mode.
@item step
Single-step to the next video frame.
@item seek @var{delta}
Seek by the given number of seconds relative to the current position.  For
example -60.0 seeks backwards one minute, and +600.0 seeks forward ten minutes.
@item set-pos @var{pos}
Seek by setting an absolute position in the stream, with @var{pos} between 0 and
1. For example, to seek to the middle of the video, use 0.5.
@item set-audio-device @var{dev}
Set the audio device to the one with the given index.
@item set-quality @var{q}
Set rendering quality, from 0 (fastest) to 4 (best, default).
@item set-stereo-mode @var{mode}
Set the stereo mode. @xref{Supported Output Techniques}.
@item set-stereo-mode-swap @var{swap}
Set stereo mode left/right swap (on or off).
@item toggle-stereo-mode-swap
Toggle stereo mode left/right swap.
@item set-crosstalk @var{cr} @var{cg} @var{cb}
Set display crosstalk levels for red, green, and blue. Each value must be between 0 and 1.
@item set-fullscreen-screens @var{screens}
Set screens to use in fullscreen mode. The value is an integer in which bits
are set for each screen that should be used (screen 1 = lowest bit). The value
0 means the default screen.
@item set-fullscreen-flip-left @var{b}
Set fullscreen flip left (on or off).
@item set-fullscreen-flop-left@var{b}
Set fullscreen flop left (on or off).
@item set-fullscreen-flip-right @var{b}
Set fullscreen flip right (on or off).
@item set-fullscreen-flop-right @var{b}
Set fullscreen flop right (on or off).
@item set-fullscreen-inhibit-screensaver @var{b}
Set fullscreen inhibit screensaver (on or off).
@item set-fullscreen-3dr-sync @var{b}
Set fullscreen DLP@registeredsymbol{} 3-D Ready Sync (on or off).
@item set-contrast @var{value}
Set contrast to the given @var{value}, from -1 to +1.
@item adjust-contrast @var{delta}
Adjust contrast by adding @var{delta}, e.g. -0.05 or +0.05.
@item set-brightness @var{value}
Set brightness to the given @var{value}, from -1 to +1.
@item adjust-brightness @var{delta}
Adjust brightness by adding @var{delta}, e.g. -0.05 or +0.05.
@item set-hue @var{value}
Set hue to the given @var{value}, from -1 to +1.
@item adjust-hue @var{delta}
Adjust hue by adding @var{delta}, e.g. -0.05 or +0.05.
@item set-saturation @var{value}
Set saturation to the given @var{value}, from -1 to +1.
@item adjust-saturation @var{delta}
Adjust saturation by adding @var{delta}, e.g. -0.05 or +0.05.
